&lt;p&gt;Sexual Health Specialist Nurse (Band 7)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sexual Health Clinic, Guildford in Surrey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey Integrated Sexual Health &amp; HIV Services at &lt;strong&gt;Buryfields Clinic&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;Guildford&lt;/strong&gt; is looking to recruit a motivated and enthusiastic registered nurse who has excellent interpersonal and communication skills along with the ability to work effectively within a multidisciplinary innovative sexual and reproductive health service. We require an individual who is forward thinking, well organised with a positive attitude towards flexibility and change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ensure that they provide a gold standard patient focused service and will be required to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the necessary clinical skills to deliver nurse led contraception and sexual health clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a high standard of care to symptomatic patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver all forms of contraception including Intrauterine Contraception and Sub-dermal implants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the ability to manage vulnerable patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support other nurses and Health Care Support Workers within the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a Nurse prescriber or willing to train&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be offered to a suitable candidate who does not meet all the criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is upto WTE 1.0 (37.5hrs) with a minimum contract of WTE 0.5 (18.75hrs).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
